Hong Kong Stocks Close 0.27 Percent Lower 
Hong Kong stocks closed 0.27 percent lower on Monday following a 1.58
percent loss on Friday.
The key Hang Seng Index fell 24.78 points, or 0.27 percent to close at
9,229.34.
The banking shares lost 59.53 points, or 0.43 percent to close at
13,636.07.
Utilities and properties dropped 0.49 percent and 0.18 percent
respectively, while commercial and industrial counters gained 10. 60
points, or 0.21 percent to close at 5,096.87.
The red-chip Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporation Index fell 1.87
percent while H-share index decreased 2.35 percent.
The turnover was 2.100 billion HK dollars (269 million U.S. dollars) as
against the 3.159 billion HK dollars (405 million U.S. dollars) on
Friday.
